\":\"ektrah/nsec\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - NSec is a new cryptographic library for .NET Core based on libsodium.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T04:57:35.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vuejs/awesome-vue","categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dev.to/denisinvader/creating-an-interactive-map-with-d3-and-vue-4158\">Creating an interactive map with D3 and Vue</a> (October 2018)</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T02:47:05.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vuejs/awesome-vue","categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.apress.com/us/book/9781484237809\">Getting to Know Vue.js</a> by Brett Nelson, Apress. (August 2018)</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T02:45:58.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ysu1989/GraphQuestions\">GraphQuestions</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ysu1989/GraphQuestions\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">80</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":80,\"repo\":\"ysu1989/GraphQuestions\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->\n<ul>\n<li>On generating Characteristic-rich Question sets for QA evaluation.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:56:38.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.msmarco.org/dataset.aspx\">MS MARCO</a>\n<ul>\n<li>This is for real-world question answering.</li>\n<li>Paper: <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.09268\">https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.09268</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:56:38.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/deepmind/narrativeqa\">NarrativeQA</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/deepmind/narrativeqa\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">379</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":379,\"repo\":\"deepmind/narrativeqa\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->\n<ul>\n<li>It includes the list of documents with Wikipedia summaries, links to full stories, and questions and answers.</li>\n<li>Paper: <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/1712.07040v1.pdf\">https://arxiv.org/pdf/1712.07040v1.pdf</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:56:38.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Maluuba/newsqa\">NewsQA</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Maluuba/newsqa\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">207</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":207,\"repo\":\"Maluuba/newsqa\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->\n<ul>\n<li>A machine comprehension dataset</li>\n<li>Paper: <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/1611.09830.pdf\">https://arxiv.org/pdf/1611.09830.pdf</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:56:38.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://rajpurkar.github.io/SQuAD-explorer/\">SQuAD1.0</a>\n<ul>\n<li>Stanford Question Answering Dataset (SQuAD) is a reading comprehension dataset, consisting of questions posed by crowdworkers on a set of Wikipedia articles, where the answer to every question is a segment of text, or span, from the corresponding reading passage, or the question might be unanswerable.</li>\n<li>Paper: <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1606.05250\">https://arxiv.org/abs/1606.05250</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:56:38.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://rajpurkar.github.io/SQuAD-explorer/\">SQuAD2.0</a>\n<ul>\n<li>SQuAD2.0 combines the 100,000 questions in SQuAD1.1 with over 50,000 new, unanswerable questions written adversarially by crowdworkers to look similar to answerable ones. To do well on SQuAD2.0, systems must not only answer questions when possible, but also determine when no answer is supported by the paragraph and abstain from answering.</li>\n<li>Paper: <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1806.03822\">https://arxiv.org/abs/1806.03822</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:56:38.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Datasets</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://nlp.cs.washington.edu/triviaqa/\">TriviaQA</a>\n<ul>\n<li>TriviaQA is a reading comprehension dataset containing over 650K question-answer-evidence triples. TriviaQA includes 95K question-answer pairs authored by trivia enthusiasts and independently gathered evidence documents, six per question on average, that provide high quality distant supervision for answering the questions.</li>\n<li>Paper: <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/1705.03551\">https://arxiv.org/abs/1705.03551</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:56:38.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Systems</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.ibm.com/watson/\">IBM Watson</a> - Has state-of-the-arts performance.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:53:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Systems</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://conceptnet.io/\">MIT media lab's Knowledge graph</a> - Is a freely-available semantic network, designed to help computers understand the meanings of words that people use.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:53:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Lectures</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/Kzi6tE4JaGo\">Question Answering - Natural Language Processing</a> - By Dragomir Radev, Ph.D. | University of Michigan | 2016.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:53:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Slides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/scottyih/Slides/blob/master/QA%20Tutorial.pdf\">Question Answering with Knowledge Bases, Web and Beyond</a> - By Scott Wen-tau Yih &#x26; Hao Ma | Microsoft Research | 2016.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:53:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Slides</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hpi.de/fileadmin/user_upload/fachgebiete/plattner/teaching/NaturalLanguageProcessing/NLP2017/NLP8_QuestionAnswering.pdf\">Question Answering</a> - By Dr. Mariana Neves | Hasso Plattner Institut | 2017.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:53:54.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"seriousran/awesome-qa","categoryHTML":"<h2>Systems</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://research.fb.com/downloads/drqa/\">Facebook DrQA</a> - Applied to the SQuAD1.0 dataset. The SQuAD2.0 dataset has released. but DrQA is not tested yet.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:51:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"avelino/awesome-go","categoryHTML":"<h2>Messaging</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/sideshow/apns2\">APNs2</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/sideshow/apns2\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2491,\"repo\":\"sideshow/apns2\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - HTTP/2 Apple Push Notification provider for Go — Send push notifications to iOS, tvOS, Safari and OSX apps.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:28:42.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"avelino/awesome-go","categoryHTML":"<h2>Miscellaneous</h2><h3>Uncategorized</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/azr/generators/tree/master/varhandler\">VarHandler</a> - Generate boilerplate http input and output handling.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-16T00:28:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"avelino/awesome-go","categoryHTML":"<h2>Software Packages</h2><h3>Other Software</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/diankong/GoDocTooltip\">GoDocTooltip</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/diankong/GoDocTooltip\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-s